<seg id=1> United States Open Enters Third Day </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Beijing, Sept. 1: According to reports from foreign news wires, the United States Open Tennis Championships entered its third day of competition on August 31. Pete Sampras, who won last year's U.S. Open, has been bothered for more than a month by an injured left ankle, but it has healed. He easily beat his opponent 3 sets to 0 to make it to the third round in men's singles. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The American Sampras, currently ranked number one in the world, has not made an appearance in competition since the middle of July. This time his injury has healed quite well, and he eliminated his South African opponent in less than an hour and a half with a third set win of 6-2 to enter the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Eighth seed Ukrainian player Andrei Medvedev beat his opponent 6-3, 6-4, 6-0 to advance to the second round. </seg>
<seg id=5> This turned out to be a present to himself for his twentieth birthday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In the women's matches, second seed Spaniard Arantxa Sanchez Vicario was challenged by her French opponent Nathalie Tauziat, but still claimed a 6-2, 7-6 victory to enter the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Fifth seed Japanese player Kimiko Date, ninth seed U.S. player Mary Joe Fernandez, and 1990 champion Argentine Gabriela Sabatini all easily defeated their opponents to advance to the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> In other news, American Michael Chang defeated his second round opponent 4-6, 6-2, 2-6, 6-3, 7-6 to advance to the third round. </seg>
</p>
